<% content_for(:title) { "Privacy Policy - Hackatime" } %>

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
  <div class="bg-white shadow rounded-lg p-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
    
    <div class="prose prose-indigo max-w-none text-gray-600">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">Last updated: <%= Date.current.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %></p>
      
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-4">What We Collect</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">When you use Hackatime, we collect:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Your Slack profile information (name, email, avatar)</li>
        <li>Your GitHub profile information (if you connect GitHub)</li>
        <li>Coding activity data (timestamps, file names, project names, languages, editors)</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-4">How We Use Your Data</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We use your data to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Display your coding statistics on your dashboard</li>
        <li>Calculate and display leaderboards</li>
        <li>Enable Slack integrations (status updates, slash commands)</li>
        <li>Link your projects to GitHub repositories</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-4">Data Retention</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We retain your coding activity data indefinitely unless you request deletion. 
        You can export or delete your data at any time by contacting us.
      </p>
      
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-4">Third Parties</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We do not sell your data. We may share anonymized, aggregated statistics 
        (e.g., total hours coded by the Hack Club community).
      </p>
      
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-4">Contact</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        For privacy-related questions, please reach out to the Hack Club team.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>